<h2><a href="/installing-pygame-python-3-mac-os-yosemite">Installing Pygame for Python 3 on Mac OS Yosemite</a></h2>
<span property="dc:title" content="Installing Pygame for Python 3 on Mac OS Yosemite" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
<div class="submitted">
<span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2014-12-20T13:36:59+08:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Submitted by <span class="username" xml:lang="" about="/users/superuser" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name" datatype="">superuser</span> on December 20, 2014 - 13:36</span> </div>
<div class="content">
<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>It's somewhat difficult to find instructions on how to successfully install Pygame for Python 3 on Yosemite. The front page of the Pygame website has a link which appears to point to installation instructions, but it is broken.</p>
<p>Fortunately, someone posted <a href="http://pygame.org/wiki/macintosh">these instructions</a> on the Pygame wiki:</p>
<p>Firstly, ensure you have the Apple Xcode command line tools installed:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">xcode-select --install
</code></pre>
<p>Install XQuartz from <a href="http://xquartz.macosforge.org/landing/">http://xquartz.macosforge.org/landing/</a>.
Restart your computer so the newly installed XQuartz is used.</p>
<p>Make sure you have <a href="http://brew.sh/">homebrew</a> installed:</p></div></div></div> </div>
<ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="/installing-pygame-python-3-mac-os-yosemite" rel="tag" title="Installing Pygame for Python 3 on Mac OS Yosemite">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about Installing Pygame for Python 3 on Mac OS Yosemite</span></a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div> </div>
</div></div>
 
</div>
</div>
 
